n="true" src="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-installed-2-1666390828947.jpg?crop=16%3A9&amp;width=158" class="jsx-2920405963 progressive-image jsx-3998823930 image aspect-ratio aspect-ratio-16-9 jsx-1330092051 jsx-3166191823 rounded" srcset="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-installed-2-1666390828947.jpg?crop=16%3A9&amp;width=158 1x, https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-installed-2-1666390828947.jpg?crop=16%3A9&amp;width=158&amp;dpr=2 2x" style="position: relative; width: 165.594px; aspect-ratio: 16 / 9; overflow: hidden; border-radius: 6px; background-color: var(--theme-elements-background-surfaceColor); display: block;"></button><button type="button" aria-label="Open Slideshow" class="jsx-3733722558 gallery-image" style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.15; margin: var(--minimumSpacer); border-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; outline-width: 0px; padding: 0px; position: relative; width: 158px; max-width: 170px; overflow: hidden; flex: 1 1 auto; min-width: 158px;"><img decoding="async" alt="" role="presentation" aria-hidden="true" src="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-outputs-1666390828948.jpg?crop=16%3A9&amp;width=158" class="jsx-2920405963 progressive-image jsx-3998823930 image aspect-ratio aspect-ratio-16-9 jsx-1330092051 jsx-3166191823 rounded" srcset="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-outputs-1666390828948.jpg?crop=16%3A9&amp;width=158 1x, https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-outputs-1666390828948.jpg?crop=16%3A9&amp;width=158&amp;dpr=2 2x" style="position: relative; width: 165.594px; aspect-ratio: 16 / 9; overflow: hidden; border-radius: 6px; background-color: var(--theme-elements-background-surfaceColor); display: block;"></button><button type="button" aria-label="Open Slideshow" class="jsx-3733722558 gallery-image" style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.15; border-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; outline-width: 0px; padding: 0px; position: relative; width: 158px; max-width: 170px; overflow: hidden; flex: 1 1 auto; min-width: 158px;"><img decoding="async" alt="" role="presentation" aria-hidden="true" src="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-vent-1666390828948.jpg?crop=16%3A9&amp;width=158" class="jsx-2920405963 progressive-image jsx-3998823930 image aspect-ratio aspect-ratio-16-9 jsx-1330092051 jsx-3166191823 rounded" srcset="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-vent-1666390828948.jpg?crop=16%3A9&amp;width=158 1x, https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-vent-1666390828948.jpg?crop=16%3A9&amp;width=158&amp;dpr=2 2x" style="position: relative; width: 165.594px; aspect-ratio: 16 / 9; overflow: hidden; border-radius: 6px; background-color: var(--theme-elements-background-surfaceColor); display: block;"></button></div></div></div></output><h2 style="font-weight: 900; margin: var(--standardSpacer) 0 var(--veryCompactSpacer);">Gigabyte Geforce RTX 4090 Gaming OC – Design and Features</h2><p style="overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis;">The Gaming OC is a monster card. That’s true of every RTX 4090 but pictures just do not do the size of these cards justice. The Gigabyte measures 13.4 x 5.9 x 3 inches, which is big enough that it flat out wouldn’t fit in my&nbsp;<a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B07MFR1VDN/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--theme-elements-text-hover); text-decoration-line: underline; text-underline-position: under;"><u>Corsair Crystal 680X</u></a>. One case upgrade later and I was finally able to install it, but it will be important to be sure your PC can support such a beefy GPU.</p><p style="margin: var(--veryCompactSpacer) 0; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis;">It’s not just length that makes this card stand out. Its three inch depth puts it squarely into quad-slot territory. That pays dividends with its cooling potential, but it may make vertical mounting difficult without pressing up against the side glass of your case and starving it of cool air. That’s a bit of a shame as Gigabyte has equipped each fan with a customizable LED ring that are all but invisible when plugged in normally.</p><a href="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-installed-1666390828947.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--theme-elements-text-hover); text-decoration-line: underline; text-underline-position: under;"><output class="article-image-container" style="font-weight: 600; padding: var(--veryCompactSpacer) 0; display: block;"><img decoding="async" alt="" role="presentation" aria-hidden="true" src="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-installed-1666390828947.jpg?fit=bounds&amp;width=1280&amp;height=720" class="jsx-2920405963 progressive-image article-image article-image-full-size jsx-2407332289 jsx-3166191823 rounded" srcset="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-installed-1666390828947.jpg?fit=bounds&amp;width=1280&amp;height=720 1x, https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-installed-1666390828947.jpg?fit=bounds&amp;width=1280&amp;height=720&amp;dpr=2 2x" style="background-color: var(--theme-elements-background-surfaceColor); border-radius: 6px; max-width: 100%; width: 876px;"></output></a><section data-transform="object-feedback"></section><p style="margin: var(--veryCompactSpacer) 0; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis;">There’s a good reason for using such a massive cooler. The RTX 4090 is a beast of a gaming card. It is designed around high performance and delivers it in spades. Like the Founders Edition, the Gaming OC features 16,384 CUDA cores, the main drivers of non-ray traced performance, and 24GB of ultra-fast GDDR6X video memory. That memory runs on a 384-bit bus and runs at 21Gbps. That’s the same as&nbsp;<a href="https://www.ign.com/articles/gigabyte-rtx-3090-ti-gaming-oc-24g-review" style="color: var(--theme-elements-text-hover); text-decoration-line: underline; text-underline-position: under;"><u>last generation’s RTX 3090 Ti</u></a>, but don’t let that fool you: this memory is wicked fast.</p><p style="margin: var(--veryCompactSpacer) 0; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis;">Stated right in the name, the Gaming OC is factory overclocked, but it’s a tiny jump over the Founders Edition. Out of the box, its boost clock comes in at 2535 MHz, which is a measly 15 MHz advantage. The memory clocks are identical at 1313 MHz. It’s an improvement but isn’t going to transform your already excellent gaming experience into something noticeably better than Nvidia’s reference card.</p><a href="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-back-1666390828948.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--theme-elements-text-hover); text-decoration-line: underline; text-underline-position: under;"><output class="article-image-container" style="font-weight: 600; padding: var(--veryCompactSpacer) 0; display: block;"><img decoding="async" alt="" role="presentation" aria-hidden="true" src="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-back-1666390828948.jpg?fit=bounds&amp;width=1280&amp;height=720" class="jsx-2920405963 progressive-image article-image article-image-full-size jsx-2407332289 jsx-3166191823 rounded" srcset="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-back-1666390828948.jpg?fit=bounds&amp;width=1280&amp;height=720 1x, https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-back-1666390828948.jpg?fit=bounds&amp;width=1280&amp;height=720&amp;dpr=2 2x" style="background-color: var(--theme-elements-background-surfaceColor); border-radius: 6px; max-width: 100%; width: 876px;"></output></a><p style="margin: var(--veryCompactSpacer) 0; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis;">But in practice, these “side of the box” specs are less important than they might at first seem. Nvidia’s GPU Boost technology intelligently ramps up all of its modern GPUs beyond these speeds anyway, so performance is constrained more by power and thermal limits than the initial tweaks manufacturers might apply. This is why aftermarket cards usually have much better thermal solutions – though the Founders Edition is excellent too – and gives AIBs a run for their money in performance per dollar.</p><p style="margin: var(--veryCompactSpacer) 0; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis;">The cooler here is something to behold. The Gaming OC uses Gigabyte’s Windforce cooling system. It’s headed by three massive 110mm fans, each imprinted with a trio of fins to better guide airflow. The middle fan spins counter to the outer two, minimizing air turbulence. Underneath is the bulk of the card’s mass, a giant heatsink lined with 10 copper heat pipes. A vapor chamber exists directly above the GPU to better draw heat into those copper pipes and out into the fins where it can be exhausted out the back. It’s essentially the same great design we saw last generation but scaled up in size. It works just as well, if not better.</p><a href="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-bios-switch-1666390828949.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--theme-elements-text-hover); text-decoration-line: underline; text-underline-position: under;"><output class="article-image-container" style="font-weight: 600; padding: var(--veryCompactSpacer) 0; display: block;"><img decoding="async" alt="" role="presentation" aria-hidden="true" src="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-bios-switch-1666390828949.jpg?fit=bounds&amp;width=1280&amp;height=720" class="jsx-2920405963 progressive-image article-image article-image-full-size jsx-2407332289 jsx-3166191823 rounded" srcset="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-bios-switch-1666390828949.jpg?fit=bounds&amp;width=1280&amp;height=720 1x, https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-bios-switch-1666390828949.jpg?fit=bounds&amp;width=1280&amp;height=720&amp;dpr=2 2x" style="background-color: var(--theme-elements-background-surfaceColor); border-radius: 6px; max-width: 100%; width: 876px;"></output></a><p style="margin: var(--veryCompactSpacer) 0; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis;">Along the back of the card is a simple but heavy duty metal backplate. It bolsters the structural integrity of the card, which feels borderline necessary with such a heavy heatsink strapped to its circuit board, but a large cutout allows for plentiful blow-through to shed heat. It’s powered by a single 16-pin port, but if your power supply doesn’t support this new standard, Gigabyte also includes an adapter to convert four eight-pin GPU plugs in an effective but ugly pigtail.</p><p style="margin: var(--veryCompactSpacer) 0; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis;">There’s also a BIOS switch to enable the factory overclock (toggled by default) or to put the card into silent mode. The card isn’t loud, even under load, and blended in with my case fans very well. The card’s silent mode will slightly raise temperatures, but as we’ll talk About in the performance section, it’s hardly something to be concerned About.</p><aside class="bordered-box jsx-4023299490 scaled" style="padding: var(--roomySpacer); border: 0.25em solid var(--theme-elements-text-default); color: var(--theme-elements-text-default); border-radius: 24px; transform: scale(0.85);"><h2 style="font-weight: 900;">What we said About the RTX 4090 Founders Edition</h2><output class="article-video-container" style="font-weight: 600; max-width: 100%; display: block; margin: var(--lessCompactSpacer) 0; border-radius: 4px; overflow: hidden;"><div class="jsx-227312401 jsx-2961976369 video-wrapper" style="--theme-elements-icon-default:var(--theme-elements-video-icon-default); --theme-elements-icon-hover:var(--theme-elements-video-icon-hover); width: 754px; display: flex; gap: var(--lessCompactSpacer);"><div class="jsx-227312401 jsx-2961976369 video-container" style="width: 754px; -webkit-box-flex: 1; flex-grow: 1;"><div class="jsx-3998823930 video aspect-ratio aspect-ratio-16-9" style="position: relative; width: 754px; aspect-ratio: 16 / 9; overflow: hidden;"><div class="jsx-3424665568 player idle" style="background-color: black; font-weight: normal; user-select: none; width: 754px;"><div class="qxyz-EY_r1E6p3k6p40Sq2Ey qxyz-CHCgHo7UG4zYGR qxyz-E3XXD3Hh" id=""><div role="presentation" class="jsx-2672688710 click-blocker hidden"><div class="jsx-2672688710 learn-more">Learn More</div></div><div class="jsx-2672688710 ad-controls hidden"><div role="presentation" aria-label="play pause toggle" class="jsx-2672688710 play playing"></div><div class="jsx-2203326644 volume-slider-container" style="height: 24px; display: flex; -webkit-box-align: center; align-items: center;"><div role="presentation" class="jsx-2203326644 volume-speaker low-volume muted" style="cursor: pointer; background-color: transparent; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-position: center center; background-size: 24px; background-image: var(--mutedVolume); width: 24px; height: 24px; position: relative; margin-right: 8px;"></div></div></div><div class="jsx-2672688710 ad-progress hidden"><div class="jsx-2672688710 current-progress" style="width: 0px; transition: width 350ms linear 0s;"></div>;</div></div><div class="jsx-2132633449 video-overlay show-background" style="height: 424.125px; width: 754px; position: absolute; z-index: 1; top: 0px; user-select: none; pointer-events: none; background: linear-gradient(rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4), rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4)) 0% 0% / 100% 100% no-repeat, url(&quot;https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/11/nvidiageforcertx4090review-36190303-rtx4090-blogroll-1665476821182.jpg&quot;);"><div class="jsx-1855809287 video-header show" style="transition: opacity 250ms ease 0s, visibility 250ms ease 0s; opacity: 1; visibility: visible; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; line-height: 22px; padding: 25px 21px; font-size: 17px; width: 754px; display: flex; -webkit-box-align: center; align-items: center; z-index: 1;"><a href="https://www.ign.com/videos/nvidia-geforce-rtx-4090-review" class="jsx-1855809287 title" style="color: var(--controlWhite); text-underline-position: under; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis; white-space: nowrap; cursor: pointer; background-image: none; user-select: none; pointer-events: auto;">Nvidia GeForce RTX 4090 Review</a></div><div class="jsx-1973000198 poster-container"><div role="presentation" class="jsx-1973000198 play" style="padding: 0px; border: none; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-position: center center; outline: none; width: 86px; height: 86px; border-radius: 50%; background-size: 102px; background-color: var(--controlWhite); background-image: var(--overlayPlayButton); position: absolute; inset: 0px; margin: auto;"></div><div class="jsx-1973000198 duration" style="color: var(--controlWhite); height: 1.8em; line-height: 1.6em; font-size: 0.9375em; text-transform: uppercase; bottom: 0px; left: 0px; margin: 1.25em; padding: 0.05em 0.6em; position: absolute; background-color: rgba(36, 37, 39, 0.85); border-radius: 0.13em; text-align: center; cursor: default;">9:01</div><div role="presentation" class="jsx-305379082 autoplay-container" style="cursor: pointer; transition: left 0.2s ease 0s, opacity 0.25s ease 0s; position: absolute; z-index: 10; pointer-events: auto; bottom: 18.75px !important; left: auto !important; right: 20px !important;"><div class="jsx-305379082 autoplay-message" style="display: inline-flex; width: 210px; padding: 10px 15px; background-color: var(--autoRenditionBackground); flex-wrap: wrap; height: 22px; border-radius: 3px; color: var(--controlWhite); font-size: 13px; line-height: 17px; -webkit-box-align: center; align-items: center; flex-direction: row-reverse !important;"><div class="jsx-305379082 autoplay-toggle" style="position: relative; width: 40px; height: 22px; border-width: 2px; border-style: solid; border-color: var(--controlWhite); border-radius: 11px;"><div class="jsx-305379082 autoplay-icon on" style="position: absolute; top: -2px; width: 22px; height: 22px; background-size: 40%; background-position: center center; background-repeat: no-repeat; border-width: 2px; border-style: solid; border-color: var(--controlWhite); border-radius: 11px; transition: right 0.1s ease 0s; right: -2px; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;base64,&quot;); background-color: var(--controlWhite);"></div></div><span class="jsx-305379082 autoplay-text" style="margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px !important;"><span class="jsx-305379082 text-left">Autoplay setting:&nbsp;</span><span class="jsx-305379082 text-right" style="font-weight: bold;">On</span></span></div></div></div></div></div></div><a href="https://www.ign.com/videos/nvidia-geforce-rtx-4090-review" class="interface jsx-425997118 bold" data-cy="video-link" style="color: inherit; text-decoration-line: underline; text-underline-position: under; font-size: var(--fontSize15); line-height: 1.5; margin: 12px auto 6px; display: block; text-align: center; user-select: none; pointer-events: auto;">Nvidia GeForce RTX 4090 Review</a></div></div></output><p style="margin: var(--veryCompactSpacer) 0; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis;">The RTX 4090 may be huge and expensive, but holy smokes if it doesn’t blow the competition out of the water. That’s a little unfair because it’s currently the only card of this new generation that’s available, so we only have cards from the past few years to compare it to. But until the rest of the pack can catch up, between its impressive hardware specs and its DLSS 3 AI wizardry, even the $1,599 price doesn’t seem unreasonable for the unrivaled frame rates that this card can crank out. -&nbsp;<em>Bo Moore and Chris Coke, October 11, 2022</em></p><h2 style="font-weight: 900; margin: var(--standardSpacer) 0 var(--veryCompactSpacer);">Score: 8</h2><p style="overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis;">Read the full&nbsp;<a href="https://www.ign.com/articles/nvidia-geforce-rtx-4090-founders-edition-review" style="color: var(--theme-elements-text-hover); text-decoration-line: underline; text-underline-position: under;">RTX 4090 Founders Edition review</a></p></aside><p style="margin: var(--veryCompactSpacer) 0; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis;">Like all RTX 4090s, the gaming OC is built on the same Ada Lovelace architecture. That means you get all of the benefits as every other model with nothing left behind. You have your streaming multiprocessor design, complete with CUDA, Tensor, and RT (ray tracing) cores, as well as new technologies like Shader Execution Reordering that improve ray tracing performance. It supports DLSS 3 and frame generation, which can dramatically improve frame rates in games that support it, like Cyberpunk 2077. Streamers and creators will also benefit from the new AV1 encoder for faster renders and improved stream quality.</p><p style="margin: var(--veryCompactSpacer) 0; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis;">For a full breakdown of these technologies, be sure to read our&nbsp;<a href="https://www.ign.com/articles/nvidia-geforce-rtx-4090-founders-edition-review" style="color: var(--theme-elements-text-hover); text-decoration-line: underline; text-underline-position: under;"><u>launch review</u></a>&nbsp;for this generation of Nvidia GPUs. There’s a lot to learn that I can only scratch the surface of here, but the Nvidia RTX 40-series is a generational leap in more ways than one.</p><a href="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-outputs-1666390828948.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--theme-elements-text-hover); text-decoration-line: underline; text-underline-position: under;"><output class="article-image-container" style="font-weight: 600; padding: var(--veryCompactSpacer) 0; display: block;"><img decoding="async" alt="" role="presentation" aria-hidden="true" src="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-outputs-1666390828948.jpg?fit=bounds&amp;width=1280&amp;height=720" class="jsx-2920405963 progressive-image article-image article-image-full-size jsx-2407332289 jsx-3166191823 rounded" srcset="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-outputs-1666390828948.jpg?fit=bounds&amp;width=1280&amp;height=720 1x, https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-outputs-1666390828948.jpg?fit=bounds&amp;width=1280&amp;height=720&amp;dpr=2 2x" style="background-color: var(--theme-elements-background-surfaceColor); border-radius: 6px; max-width: 100%; width: 876px;"></output></a><p style="margin: var(--veryCompactSpacer) 0; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis;">For outputs, the card features three DisplayPort 1.4 ports and one HDMI 2.1 connection. It supports a maximum resolution of 7680x4320 (8K) across all four ports.</p><h2 style="font-weight: 900; margin: var(--standardSpacer) 0 var(--veryCompactSpacer);">Gigabyte Geforce RTX 4090 Gaming OC – Performance</h2><p style="overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis;">Before diving into our benchmark results, it’s worth taking a closer look at the factory overclock Gigabyte has applied here. As I discussed in the section above, the rated out of box speed is only 15 MHz faster than the 2.52 GHz found on the Founders Edition, but with GPU Boost factored in, things change considerably.</p><p style="margin: var(--veryCompactSpacer) 0; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis;">In my testing, the card reached a peak clock speed of 2760 MHz but settled in at 2745 MHz while gaming. What’s especially interesting is that the Founder’s Edition achieved a higher peak speed of 2775 MHz but also settled in at 2760 MHz after that initial boost. In practice, overclocked or not, the average clock speed was the same on both cards.</p><a href="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-installed-2-1666390828947.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--theme-elements-text-hover); text-decoration-line: underline; text-underline-position: under;"><output class="article-image-container" style="font-weight: 600; padding: var(--veryCompactSpacer) 0; display: block;"><img decoding="async" alt="" role="presentation" aria-hidden="true" src="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-installed-2-1666390828947.jpg?fit=bounds&amp;width=1280&amp;height=720" class="jsx-2920405963 progressive-image article-image article-image-full-size jsx-2407332289 jsx-3166191823 rounded" srcset="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-installed-2-1666390828947.jpg?fit=bounds&amp;width=1280&amp;height=720 1x, https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/gigabyte-rtx-4090-gaming-oc-24g-installed-2-1666390828947.jpg?fit=bounds&amp;width=1280&amp;height=720&amp;dpr=2 2x" style="background-color: var(--theme-elements-background-surfaceColor); border-radius: 6px; max-width: 100%; width: 876px;"></output></a><p style="margin: var(--veryCompactSpacer) 0; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis;">The Gaming OC did win in temperatures, however. While the Founders Edition hit a peak temp of 64.7C, the Gigabyte topped out at 62C under heavy load and oscillated between 60-61C while gaming. With the Silent Bios enabled, that temperature jumped up to 65C, putting it on par with the FE. If you have the extra juice in your power supply, it’s a perfect fit for manual overclocking.</p><p style="margin: var(--veryCompactSpacer) 0; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis;">That said, unless you’re looking to eke every last ounce of performance from the card, it’s probably not necessary. Even at 4K, the RTX 4090 Gaming OC 24G offers stellar frame rates and smooth, responsive gameplay.</p><p style="margin: var(--veryCompactSpacer) 0; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis;">Let’s get into the benchmark results.</p><aside class="bordered-box jsx-4023299490 scaled" style="padding: var(--roomySpacer); border: 0.25em solid var(--theme-elements-text-default); color: var(--theme-elements-text-default); border-radius: 24px; transform: scale(0.85);"><p style="overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis;"><em>Test system: MSI MEG Z670E ACE, Ryzen 9 7950X (stock), Corsair iCUE H150i ELITE LCD Display Liquid CPU Cooler, 32GB Corsair Vengeance RGB Pro DDR5-6000, 2TB Gigabyte AORUS NVMe SSD, 1200 Watt ASUS THOR power supply.</em></p></aside><a href="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/3dmark-1666390926347.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--theme-elements-text-hover); text-decoration-line: underline; text-underline-position: under;"><output class="article-image-container" style="font-weight: 600; padding: var(--veryCompactSpacer) 0; display: block;"><img decoding="async" alt="" role="presentation" aria-hidden="true" src="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/3dmark-1666390926347.jpg?fit=bounds&amp;width=1280&amp;height=720" class="jsx-2920405963 progressive-image article-image article-image-full-size jsx-2407332289 jsx-3166191823 rounded" srcset="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/3dmark-1666390926347.jpg?fit=bounds&amp;width=1280&amp;height=720 1x, https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/3dmark-1666390926347.jpg?fit=bounds&amp;width=1280&amp;height=720&amp;dpr=2 2x" style="background-color: var(--theme-elements-background-surfaceColor); border-radius: 6px; max-width: 100%; width: 876px;"></output></a><p style="margin: var(--veryCompactSpacer) 0; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis;">Beginning with 3DMark Fire Strike Ultra, we see the three 4090s in this test easily outperform last generation’s flagships. Note that the score pulled in by the Gaming OC is higher overall due to differences in our test systems but the graphics performance of all three cards is nearly identical. Neck and neck performance in this test.</p><a href="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/unigine-heaven-1666390940146.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--theme-elements-text-hover); text-decoration-line: underline; text-underline-position: under;"><output class="article-image-container" style="font-weight: 600; padding: var(--veryCompactSpacer) 0; display: block;"><img decoding="async" alt="" role="presentation" aria-hidden="true" src="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/unigine-heaven-1666390940146.jpg?fit=bounds&amp;width=1280&amp;height=720" class="jsx-2920405963 progressive-image article-image article-image-full-size jsx-2407332289 jsx-3166191823 rounded" srcset="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/unigine-heaven-1666390940146.jpg?fit=bounds&amp;width=1280&amp;height=720 1x, https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/unigine-heaven-1666390940146.jpg?fit=bounds&amp;width=1280&amp;height=720&amp;dpr=2 2x" style="background-color: var(--theme-elements-background-surfaceColor); border-radius: 6px; max-width: 100%; width: 876px;"></output></a><p style="margin: var(--veryCompactSpacer) 0; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis;">The second synthetic test in our round-up is Unigine Heaven. Like 3DMark, it renders a series of scenes that push GPU performance above all else, so the scores here can shed some light on how similar models of GPU compare. At 4K, the Gigabyte falls slightly behind, but manages to pull a lead over both the Founder Edition and the MSI RTX 4090 Suprim Liquid X.</p><a href="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/ray-tracing-synthetics-1666390951568.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--theme-elements-text-hover); text-decoration-line: underline; text-underline-position: under;"><output class="article-image-container" style="font-weight: 600; padding: var(--veryCompactSpacer) 0; display: block;"><img decoding="async" alt="" role="presentation" aria-hidden="true" src="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/ray-tracing-synthetics-1666390951568.jpg?fit=bounds&amp;width=1280&amp;height=720" class="jsx-2920405963 progressive-image article-image article-image-full-size jsx-2407332289 jsx-3166191823 rounded" srcset="https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/ray-tracing-synthetics-1666390951568.jpg?fit=bounds&amp;width=1280&amp;height=720 1x, https://assets-prd.ignimgs.com/2022/10/21/ray-tracing-synthetics-1666390951568.jpg?fit=bounds&amp;width=1280&amp;height=720&amp;dpr=2 2x" style="background-color: var(--theme-elements-background-surfaceColor); border-radius: 6px; max-width: 100%; width: 876px;"></output></a><p style="margin: var(--veryCompactSpacer) 0; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis;">Ray tracing performance pulls the competition tighter across the board. In the Boundary ray tracing benchmark, the three cards split the difference between 82 and 84 FPS. In 3DMark’s Port Royal ray tracing test, it scores 2% higher than the RTX 4090 Founders Edition but is About 350 points, or 1.4%, behind the MSI Suprim Liquid X. In 3DMark’s Ray Tracing Test, the story is much the same. It’s two frames shy of the Suprim but one frame ahead of the FE.</p><output class="widget-container" style="font-weight: 600; max-width: 100%; padding: var(--veryCompactSpacer) 0; display: block;"><div class="jsx-3733722558 slideshow-preview"><div class="jsx-3733722558 title" style="margin: var(--veryCompactSpacer) 0;">Gigabyte Geforce RTX 4090 Gaming OC – Gaming Benchmarks</div><div class="jsx-3733722558 images-container"><button type="button" aria-label="Open Slideshow" class="jsx-3733722558 hero-image" st